    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName>4 Wimpole Street, Cavendish Square, London</placeName>
                        <date>Feby 2d 1836</date>
                        <salute>My Dear Sir,</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">

                  <p>I write merely to say to you that the amounts placed to my account at Mess. Payne &amp; Smith, of ninety-four pounds 19/6 - was duly paid, and I beg of you to accept my sincerest thanks for your kind attentions.</p>
                  <p>I have already written to the honobe Mr Granville, explanatory as yourself mentioned, but although many many months have elapsed, not a word has been received from him in reply.</p>
                  <p>Believe me My Dear Sir</p>
                  <p>Your ever truly obliged and</p>
                  <p>Obt Sevt</p>
                  <p>John J. Audubon</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </body>
